RACE.FOOTNOTES: CAIRO SUGAR two to three wide in closest aim of the leader, advanced to knock heads with that rival before taking sole command near the half mile pole, tucked inside through the turn and shook away, got roused taking the inside route into upper stretch, drew off under a light drive to prevail. TWO REDHEADS stumbled at the start, chased three then two wide under coaxing from the five-sixteenths, spun three wide for home, proved no match for the top one while running on to secure the place honors. DREAM ON CARA coaxed from the gate, chased three then two wide under coaxing from the three-eighths, spun three wide for home, kept on to procure the show honors. THE SPLENDID ONE chased just off the inside until tucked inside through the turn, came under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, spun just off the inside for home and weakened. LAVON coaxed from the start, chased four then three wide under a ride from the three-eighths, swung four wide for home and weakened. BERNING HONOR showed the way in hand along the inside under pressure from the eventual winner, conceded the front near the half mile pole and chased along the inside through the turn coaxed along from the seven-sixteenths and fading, went five wide into upper stretch, folded, and was eased home to the finish.

BUSTIN BAY broke out and brushed with a foe then was quickly corrected while coming out in front, led for the opening sixteenth-pole then pressed between rivals, took a brief advantage for two strides inside the seven-sixteenths then lost the lead to the winner, shifted five wide while losing touch with that opponent into the stretch, moved out in pursuit of that foe around the three-sixteenths and tired while well clear for third. CARAMOCHA was coaxed to the front after going a sixteenth, set the pace under pressure to her outside, lost the lead while along the rail inside the seven-sixteenths, dropped back coming to the five-sixteenths and stopped.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: DOUBLE SHOT chased just off the inside down the backstretch before tucking inside through the turn coming under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, went seven wide into upper stretch, rallied to issue a challenge through the final furlong and was up in the last jumps to score. MASKED MARAUDER chased five then four wide coming under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, swung five wide for home, rallied to take command near the eighth pole, dug in under threat and was caught in the final strides to the wire.
